author: kfogel
msg: * subversion/libsvn_client/diff.c (diff_cmd): Renamed from
svn_client__diff_cmd; the function is static and shouldn't use the
"svn_client__" prefix, which is for shared private symbols.
All callers changed.

(usage): Sorted (again) into alphabetical order the subcommands.

author: kfogel
msg: * subversion/clients/cmdline/commit-cmd.c (message_from_editor): Use
apr_file_write_full, not apr_file_write; if the latter were used, it
would have had to be in a loop.  Use APR_STATUS_IS_SUCCESS to check
return code.  Separate return code check from bytes-written check,
with a distinct error for each case.  Return real errors instead of a
bogus NULL (which should have been APR_STATUS_IS_SUCCESS in this
context anyway).  Fix up some formatting in the immediate vicinity.
Have not touched other stuff in this file, leaving that for Daniel.
Note the same problem with apr_file_write vs apr_file_full_write in
print_short_format.
